<td width="602" valign="top">
	<img src="/images/spacer.gif" width="602" height="1">
    <h1>Texas Pecan Growers</h1>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">The Texas Pecan Growers Association (TPGA) is a nonprofit, educational association, formed in 1921 and incorporated in 1967. &nbsp;The TPGA Mission is: To assist Texas pecan growers in growing pecans profitably through education, research, and promotion of consumption.<span style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>
<hr />
<h2>Texas Pecan Trail</h2>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">This holiday season, TPGA created a Texas Pecan Trail to showcase as many of our pecan retail stores as possible. Use this map to find a retail store near you or a location you are visiting soon!</span></p>
<p><br /> <iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/2/embed?mid=1TqcmH5_GSObeYN0uGC5ChVHsdVHzqYIL" width="640" height="480"></iframe></p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong><span>Thank you for all those who attended the Texas Pecan Growers Association 97th Annual Conference and Trade Show! Mark your calendars for next year's conference on July 14-17, 2019 in Frisco, Texas.</span><br /></strong></span></p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;<span style="font-size: small;">To help carry out our mission, TPGA publishes a monthly magazine, <a style="font-size: 10px;" href="pecansouthmagazine.com" target="_blank">Pecan South,</a> which is distributed by subscription nationally and to a number of foreign countries. Pecan South is included with membership in TPGA. TPGA also publishes The Pecan Newsletter each fall during the harvest season to keep growers updated on current market conditions. To subscribe to either of these publications, visit our web store or call our office.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">TPGA's Annual Conference and Trade Show takes place each July and offers an extensive educational program, oftentimes an orchard tour, and a pecan trade show featuring machinery and equipment vendors, irrigation companies, pecan nurseries, chemical distributors and much more. You'll find more information on this annual event on the annual conference page.</span></p>
<hr />
<p><span style="font-size: small;">A message to our members: If you are trying to renew your membership or if you want to create a new membership, you must complete that transaction through this website&mdash;tpga.org. Pecan South magazine has a new website, but that site is only for the magazine. Any orders completed through that site will be for the magazine, not for membership.&nbsp;</span></p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<p><img title="Texas Pecan Growers is proud to be a GO TEXAN member." src="images/goTexan.gif" alt="Texas Pecan Growers is proud to be a GO TEXAN member." width="65" align="left" /><span style="font-size: small;">TPGA is proud to be a <strong>GO TEXAN</strong> member and we encourage Texas pecan growers to <strong>"GO TEXAN"</strong>. <a href="http://www.gotexan.org" target="_blank">Click here to find out how.</a></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
